Introduction

D-art was a South Korean girl group which was formed from the competition DIMA K-Pop Season 1, hosted by Dong-ah Institute of Media and Arts (DIMA). The line-up consists of Eunsu, Yu1l, Hwanhee and PiA. They debuted on January 10, 2022 with Cinderella. The girl group disbanded sometime after the release of "Cinderella", though it is known that members Je Hwanhee and Yu1L became members of another project girl group in 2023, ONEST, also formed through Dong-ah Institute.
